additional_house_rules:
This is your beautiful home away from home and there are a few house rules to keep it warm and wonderful for every guest that walks through the door.

New York is an old city and these are old buildings so please remember to take extra care regarding the toilet/plumbing!

Please be sure to use the recycling bins inside the apartment as well as placing them in the proper section outside - it is against the law here to not recycle and you will receive a hefty fine from the police department if you don't recycle properly! 

No smoking 

Please remember to turn off the AC and unplug the twinkle lights and neon sign when you leave

Please refrain from burning candles 

Please don't flush anything besides toilet paper down the toilet

Please no loud music or parties - the apartment building is filled with young professionals and it's important to be respectful! 


Please do not move the furniture around - put everything back the way you found it upon your departure 

I like to have total transparency with my guests so here is some information I'd like you to have:
The super intendant of our building is a little nosy - if anyone asks you if you are renting my apartment tell them no and that you are friends of mine that are just house sitting for me.  Again, if anyone asks, you are not paying for your stay at my apartment, you are friends of mine and you are house sitting for free. It will make everyone's life much easier! I have never yet had any problems with guests in this situation but I want to make sure you have all the information you need before making your decision! Please feel free to message me if you have questions or concerns about this. 

Please treat this space as your home away from home so that it can remain warm and wonderful for all future guests! Thank you!
description:
This chic cozy studio located in the heart of midtown Manhattan is a dream space for anyone looking to enjoy everything the big apple has to offer.  A clean, calm oasis that is mere steps from: all the Broadway theaters, Times Square, Shopping, dining, nightlife and much much more!

Cozy corner unit studio that gets tons of natural light due to the three large windows throughout the space.  This apartment is perfectly located - it's in the heart of exciting Mid-Town West but situated on a quiet residential block.  There is a brand new stainless steel refrigerator, a convection oven, a microwave and a dishwasher. A ton of closet and drawer space.  The bathroom features a brand new spa shower head.  It is a calm, secure oasis in the middle of the bustling city. It's the ideal spot to enjoy the holiday season in the big apple!

Guests can enjoy:
Apple TV
Fast Wifi
A professionally decorated space
Black-out curtains
Pillow top bed
Comfy pull-out couch
Luxe towels and linens
New air conditioning unit
Fully functioning kitchen complete with everything you would need to cook a delicious meal! Dishwasher, stainless steel refrigerator, convection oven and microwave

Guests can reach me 24 hours a day via email or text

Hell's Kitchen is a bright, vibrant neighborhood in the heart of the theater district.  There are endless choices for every type of delicious cuisine imaginable as well as some of the highest rated bars in the city.  This is also a very LGBTQ friendly neighborhood and boasts some of the city's most fabulous gay bars.  In addition to all of the bars, restaurants, and entertainment, all of the services you need for comfortable daily living are just around the corner.  

You are mere steps away from:
Every Broadway theater (and some off-Broadway theaters as well)
Times Square
Incredible restaurants 
Fantastic bars
Shopping
Central Park
Lincoln Center
Columbus Circle 
Movie Theaters
The world's best mass transit system
CVS
Whole Foods Market
Urgent Care 
ZipCar lots
CitiBike

This apartment is a transportation dream!
Within walking distance of:
Almost every subway line in NYC
Port Authority Bus Station
Zipcar lot (a block away)
CitiBike lot (on the same block)

If you prefer to walk (like a true New Yorker!) you are within walking distance of the entire Theater District, Lincoln Center area, Times Square, Rockefeller Center (the tree and skating rink are a must see!), Bryant Park, Herald Square, The Upper West Side, Columbus Circle Shopping Center, Central Park and much much more!

This studio is your home away from home in the big city and comes fully stocked with all the essentials you may need for your stay:

There are fresh linens and towels in the hall closet
Please help yourself to the jar of beauty goodies in the bathroom
Please help yourself to any snacks and drinks you find in the refrigerator and cupboard
All dirty laundry can be placed in the white mesh laundry basket in the closet
The apartment is located on the second floor of the building (no elevator) it's 1 flight up.

review.comments: Our stay was great! Couldn't have asked for anything better. The apartment is within walking distance to everything. Like others have noted, it can be a little noisy at night, but that would be anywhere. The apartment fit the two of us and all of our things for a week. It was clean and had everything we could have needed and more! Rachel is a great host and she responded quickly to everything we needed. Thanks for the great stay!
